Mine rescue vehicles are essential in emergency situations in mining operations where workers may be trapped due to accidents, fires, or other hazardous conditions. The global mine rescue vehicle market is segmented by type, capacity, and region. Based on type, the market is divided into wheeled mine rescue vehicles and tracked mine rescue vehicles. Wheeled mine rescue vehicles are more maneuverable and suitable for terrains with better infrastructure, while tracked mine rescue vehicles offer better traction in challenging environments. In terms of capacity, mine rescue vehicles are categorized as accommodating up to 10 people, 10-20 people, and more than 20 people, depending on the size of the rescue operation. Regionally, the market is analyzed across North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, and the Middle East and Africa.

